Sukoluhle Ndlovu Midlands Correspondent Two agricultural inputs clerks employed by Cottco in Gokwe have been arrested after they allegedly stole 30 tonnes of fertiliser allocated under Command Agriculture and sold the loot in Harare. The duo, Ropafadzo Mucheli (20) and Darlington Senan (35), today appeared before Gokwe Magistrate Christopher Maturure charged with fraud and theft. They both pleaded guilty to the charges and were remanded in custody to December 21 for sentencing. Details to followâ€¦